# Add files here to ignore them from prettier formatting

/dist
/coverage
/.nx/cache

# Generated cross-surface mirrors — written ONLY by the sync pipeline
# (codex:sync / copilot:sync). These are byte-compared against their canonical
# sources by the mirror-equality verifiers (verify-skill-protocol-compliance,
# verify-sync-divergence, verify-copilot-divergence). If prettier reformats them
# they drift out of byte-equality with their source and the verifiers FAIL — the
# exact drift that broke this repo when `prettier --write AGENTS.md` ran standalone.
# The sync is the SOLE writer of these bytes; never hand-edit or prettier them.
# (CLAUDE.md is intentionally NOT here — it is prettier-managed source. The generator
#  does NOT run prettier itself: the .claude pipeline stays node_modules-free / portable,
#  so it emits raw markdown (un-padded tables). Run `prettier --write CLAUDE.md` after any
#  `claude-md` regen and BEFORE `codex:sync`, or AGENTS.md embeds the un-padded body and
#  later drifts from a prettier pass — the exact byte-drift the divergence verifiers catch.)
/AGENTS.md
/.codex/
/.agents/
/.github/copilot-instructions.md
/.github/instructions/

# C# files - use dotnet format instead (respects .editorconfig)
*.cs
*.csx
